<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">PART I&mdash;STATEMENT OF FACTS</TI>
<P>1. The Applicant's Affidavit was due to be served on June 4, 2014.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Affidavit of Lindsey Ash sworn July 11, 2014 (&ldquo;Ash Affidavit&rdquo;), para. 2, Respondent's Motion Record, pp. 5</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P>2. On June 19, 2014, the Applicant's Affidavit was received at the Department of Justice Canada office in Halifax, Nova Scotia.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Ash Affidavit para. 3 and Exhibit A, Respondent's Motion Record, pp. 5 &amp; 8</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P>3. On June 19, 2014, counsel for the Respondent, wrote to the Applicant and advised him that the Respondent had received his Affidavit, which was due on June 4, 2014. She further advised him that she consented to an extension of 15 days to have the Applicant's Affidavit served and advised the Applicant to provide the letter with proof of service to the Court.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Ash Affidavit, para. 4 and Exhibit B, Respondent's Motion Record, pp. 5 &amp; 21</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P>4. The Applicant late filed his Affidavit of Service confirming service of his Affidavit and the Federal Court Registry in Toronto did not accept the Applicant's Affidavit of Service.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Ash Affidavit, para. 5 and Exhibit C, Respondent's Motion Record, pp. 6 &amp; 23</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P>5. On July 9, 2014, the Respondent served the Applicant with its Affidavit pursuant to Rule 307 of the <EM>Federal Courts Rules</EM> by courier. The Respondent filed the Solicitor's Certificate of Service on July 9, 2014.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Ash Affidavit, para. 6 and Exhibit D, Respondent's Motion Record, pp. 6 &amp; 26</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P>6. Counsel for the Respondent received a telephone call from Elizabeth Caverly, the Director of the Courts Administrative Service of the Federal Court in Halifax, Nova Scotia on July 10, 2014. Ms. Caverly advised counsel that the Respondent had late filed proof of service of the Respondent's Affidavit. She further advised that the Applicant's Affidavit of Service had not been accepted for filing by the Federal Court Registry in Toronto.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Ash Affidavit, para. 7, Respondent's Motion Record, pp. 6</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P>7. Until advised by Ms. Caverly that the Applicant's Affidavit of Service had not been accepted for filing, the Respondent was not aware that the date for service of the Respondent's Affidavit was to be calculated based on the original due date of the Applicant's Affidavit, being June 4, 2014 and not the extended date consented to by the Respondent, being June 19, 2014.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Ash Affidavit, para. 8, Respondent's Motion Record, pp. 6</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">PART II&mdash;LAW</TI>
<P>8. Pursuant to Rule 307 of the <EM>Federal Courts Rules</EM>, SOR/98-106 (the &ldquo;<EM>Rules</EM>&rdquo;), the Respondent's Affidavit is due to be served within 30 days after service of the Applicant's Affidavit.</P>
<P>9. Pursuant to Rule 8 of the <EM>Rules</EM>, an Application for Extension of Time may be made to the Court before or after the end of the period sought to be extended.</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="III">PART III&mdash;SUBMISSIONS</TI>
<P>10. The Respondent submits that both parties have received the other party's Affidavit and therefore there has been no undue delay in this matter, and there is no prejudice in the failure by either party to serve their Affidavit within the thirty day time limit.</P>
<P>11. The Respondent submits that the facts show that there is proper justification for requiring the extension of time to serve the affidavits. The Respondent has requested an extension as soon as it became aware of the need to do so.</P>
<P>12. He farther submits that the Affidavits are necessary to properly canvas the issues in this application.</P>
<P>13. The Respondent submits that justice requires that the extension be granted and, therefore requests that this application be allowed.</P>
<P>14. For the reasons set out above, the Respondent does not oppose the granting of an extension to the Applicant to serve his affidavit and file proof of service pursuant to Rule 306, should such a request be made.</P>
<P><BOLD>ALL OF WHICH IS RESPECTFULLY SUBMITTED</BOLD></P>
<P>Dated at the Regional Municipality of Halifax this 11<SUP>th</SUP> day of July, 2014.</P>
