<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT OF LINDSEY ASH</TI>
<P>I, Lindsey Ash, of the Regional Municipality of Halifax, in the Province of Nova Scotia, MAKE OATH AND SAY THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am employed as a Legal Assistant, with the Tax Law Services Section, Department of Justice Canada in the Atlantic Regional Office and as such have personal knowledge of the matters hereinafter deposed to, save and except what is stated to be on information and belief, and where so stated, I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. The Applicant's Affidavit was due to be served on June 4, 2014.</P>
<P>3. On June 19, 2014, the Applicant's affidavit was received at the Department of Justice office in Halifax, Nova Scotia. A true copy of the Affidavit, with date stamped tab, is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P>4. On June 19, 2014, Caitlin Ward, Counsel of record in this application, wrote to the Applicant and advised him that the Respondent had received his affidavit, which was due on June 4, 2014. She further advised him that she consented to an extension of 15 days to have the Applicant's affidavit served and advised the Applicant to provide the letter with proof of service to the Court. A copy of the letter sent by Caitlin Ward on June 19, 2014 is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P>5. I have reviewed the online Federal Court Registry records with respect to this application. The online information shows that the Applicant late filed his Affidavit of Service confirming service of his Affidavit and that the Federal Court Registry in Toronto did not accept the Applicant's Affidavit of Service. A true copy of the online Federal Court Registry record with respect to this application is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>6. On July 9, 2014, the Respondent served the Applicant with its Affidavit pursuant to Rule 307 of the <EM>Federal Courts Rules</EM> by courier. The Respondent filed the Solicitor's Certificate of Service on July 9, 2014. A true copy of the letter to the Applicant dated July 9, 2014, without attachments and the solicitor's certificate of service filed by the Respondent are attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>7. I am advised by Caitlin Ward, and do verily believe, that she received a telephone call from Elizabeth Caverly, the Director of the Courts Administrative Service of the Federal Court in Halifax, Nova Scotia on July 10, 2014. Ms. Caverly advised Ms. Ward that the Respondent had late filed proof of service of the Respondent's affidavit. She further advised that the Applicant's Affidavit of Service had not been accepted for filing by the Federal Court Registry in Toronto.</P>
<P>8. Until advised by Ms. Caverly that the Applicant's Affidavit of Service had not been accepted for filing, the Respondent was not aware that the date for service of the Respondent's affidavit was to be calculated based on the original due date of the Applicant's Affidavit, being June 4, 2014 and not the extended date consented to by the Respondent, being June 19, 2014.</P>
