<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">PART 1&mdash;STATEMENT OF FACTS</TI>
<P>1] Around the end of August i called Caitlin Ward as i could see time for Respondents counsel filing was very late and was concerned of the next steps and making sure i had and was following procedures of which upon going down to the filing office on Queen St, Toronto [after leaving a message] i found i had.</P>
<P>2] This filing office informed me that i should file an Applicants record ASAP as given that the time for CRA's filing of proof of service was really late that my time to file Applicants record was almost up. So i spent time at internet doing this and was about to file it as only a few days left when i received CRA's counsel's request for extension and explanation.</P>
<P>3] I do not feel that inadvertence is a good excuse to grant this extension. Caitlin Ward is a very experienced lawyer who specifically deals with these matters all the time and knows the exact time periods to file[unlike myself who is new to this and does not have a lawyer] She stated that she had &ldquo;forgotten' and that without my phone call she would have not realized period. This is a very poor reason to grant an extension and has only delayed this procedure by at least a couple of months and i am the only one who suffers from it as i am in a very precarious state of survival right now given my accident and huge loss of income this relief application is huge for me</P>
<P>4] After rushing down to the CRA filing office and discovering that i had only a few days to file an Applicants Record-as i was advised i needed to do ASAP by them given that due to CRA not filing affidavit of service, a Cross Examination was no longer needed or part of the process.. I felt like this possibly was done on purpose as CRA lawyers know i am inexperienced and doing this on my own and put me in a panic position. If i had not walked into that office there was a strong chance that by CRA &ldquo;forgetting&rdquo; to file that i was the one who would pay for it</P>
<P>5] We should already be past the applicants record stage and we are not and it is only because of an experienced lawyer forgetting and wants to be saved only because I called.</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">PART 2&mdash;LAW</TI>
<P>6] Rule 8 for an Application for Extension of Time can also deny the extension if reasons unreasonable</P>
